  "title": "Economic support ratios and the demographic dividend in Europe",
  "abstract": "Support ratios and dependency ratios are widely used as indicators for measuring the effects of population ageing on economic development. Both of these indicators use fixed age limits to distinguish between the working and the dependent populations.",
